Three main numerical scenarios were investigated in this study. First, a homogeneous viscoelastic body was modeled using selected material parameters, reported in Table 1
                        . Specifically, the following tissue-mimicking homogeneous phantoms were considered:

                              •

Elastic: characterized by one parameter (Fig. 2
                                 a);


                              •

Kelvin–Voigt: characterized by two parameters (Fig. 2b);


                              •

Maxwell: characterized by two parameters (Fig. 2c);


                              •

Zener: characterized by three parameters (Fig. 2d);


                              •

Burgers: characterized by four parameters (Fig. 2e);


                              •

Maxwell–Wiechert (for N = 2): characterized by five parameters (Fig. 2f).
